message.text:
Exactly three years ago, my expected college life took a 180° turn. It was during TamHunt 2023 — the first time the Tamaraws witnessed 𝐳𝟑𝐭𝐚, the drag persona who would eventually help me meet and embrace Amber even more.

Growing up, being effeminate was something a few of my relatives treated almost like a mortal sin. But I chose not to let their words define me. I knew deep inside that my truest expression came alive through makeup brushes. At first, I thought my desire to look hyperfeminine and “woman-like” was just a phase — but in reality, it was a calling. Drag was never just an outlet for creativity; it became the bridge that revealed the woman within me to the world.

From performing a piece so close to my heart under the small spotlight of FEU SAGA, to standing proudly on the stage of One Concierto Piyu alongside my sisters — I can’t put into words how grateful I am for the people who pushed me to keep going, no matter the circumstances.

This is for the little me who didn’t know she loved herself yet. Know that I am so proud of you little Amber.

Love,

Your favorite trans-alternative diva, 𝐳𝟑𝐭𝐚

message.text:
Exactly three years ago, my expected college life took a 180° turn. It was during TamHunt 2023 — the first time the Tamaraws witnessed 𝐳𝟑𝐭𝐚, the drag persona who would eventually help me meet and embrace Amber even more.

Growing up, being effeminate was something a few of my relatives treated almost like a mortal sin. But I chose not to let their words define me. I knew deep inside that my truest expression came alive through makeup brushes. At first, I thought my desire to look hyperfeminine and “woman-like” was just a phase — but in reality, it was a calling. Drag was never just an outlet for creativity; it became the bridge that revealed the woman within me to the world.

From performing a piece so close to my heart under the small spotlight of FEU SAGA, to standing proudly on the stage of One Concierto Piyu alongside my sisters — I can’t put into words how grateful I am for the people who pushed me to keep going, no matter the circumstances.

This is for the little me who didn’t know she loved herself yet. Know that I am so proud of you little Amber.

Love,

Your favorite trans-alternative diva, 𝐳𝟑𝐭𝐚

message.text:
Exactly three years ago, my expected college life took a 180° turn. It was during TamHunt 2023 — the first time the Tamaraws witnessed 𝐳𝟑𝐭𝐚, the drag persona who would eventually help me meet and embrace Amber even more.

Growing up, being effeminate was something a few of my relatives treated almost like a mortal sin. But I chose not to let their words define me. I knew deep inside that my truest expression came alive through makeup brushes. At first, I thought my desire to look hyperfeminine and “woman-like” was just a phase — but in reality, it was a calling. Drag was never just an outlet for creativity; it became the bridge that revealed the woman within me to the world.

From performing a piece so close to my heart under the small spotlight of FEU SAGA, to standing proudly on the stage of One Concierto Piyu alongside my sisters — I can’t put into words how grateful I am for the people who pushed me to keep going, no matter the circumstances.

This is for the little me who didn’t know she loved herself yet. Know that I am so proud of you little Amber.

Love,

Your favorite trans-alternative diva, 𝐳𝟑𝐭𝐚

message.text:
𝐒𝐩𝐞𝐜𝐢𝐚𝐥 𝐝𝐞𝐥𝐢𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐲! 𝐘𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐢𝐧𝐛𝐨𝐱 𝐣𝐮𝐬𝐭 𝐠𝐨𝐭 𝐚 𝐦𝐞𝐬𝐬𝐚𝐠𝐞, 𝐘’𝐞𝐫𝐬! 📩🧡

Have you checked your inbox yet? Your leadership role awaits you! The mail about your next big step is officially out! 💌

Y'ers, we thank you for stepping up and embracing the challenge. ♾️

This year, we’re not just soaring high— we’re defying limits, nagCYCibol sa HimPAMPawid, and building a legacy that lasts beyond today. 💥

We can't wait to see you!🙈🫵🏻

#CYCibolSaHimPAMPawid
#DefyingLimits
#TheLegaCYContinues
#CYC27
#TamHunt2025 

Caption by Alexine Medenilla, Stephanie Ashley Buenaventura
Publication Material by LJ Rocha
